Cypseloides niger) - a species of birds of the swift family. The largest swift north of Mexico and the northernmost of the American swifts. It lives along the Pacific coast of North America from Alaska to Mexico, it is also found on the Atlantic coast of Mexico. In Central America, birds live in the territory from the Costa -Riki to Guatemala and Honduras, on many islands of the West Indies. The exact wintering places of the black american swift are unknown, migration can be up to 7 thousand kilometers.